id: pm-1ybs
title: "Lazy-load @sentry/node off the command hot path (~850ms ESM load on every command, even when telemetry disabled)"
description: ""
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[2]: performance,telemetry
created_at: "2026-07-12T13:20:06.786Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-12T15:42:31.235Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-12T15:42:10.861Z"
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: "Static import of @sentry/node in src/core/sentry/instrument.ts replaced by a dynamic import that runs only after the isSentryDisabled() gate; PM_SENTRY_DISABLED=1 / PM_TELEMETRY_DISABLED=1 / vitest runs never load the Sentry module graph; Telemetry-enabled runs preserve current behavior: init fires at command start (non-blocking), error-capture and flush paths await the same init promise, spans/breadcrumbs still emitted; pm list wall time at the current workspace drops from ~1.4s to <=0.85s (stub-experiment ceiling 562-801ms); measured before/after recorded on pm-mi2x; Full test suite + contract tests green; zero flag/output changes"
risk: medium
confidence: high
resolution: Deferred the Sentry runtime module graph until after telemetry opt-out guards while preserving enabled capture and flush semantics.
expected_result: "Disabled commands avoid loading @sentry/node; enabled telemetry initializes, captures, spans, breadcrumbs, and flushes as before with lower command startup latency."
actual_result: "48 focused tests passed, the live Sentry/telemetry gate passed, and scale dogfood demonstrated the reduced read-path cost with zero flag/output contract change."
