close_reason: Removed the static Sentry module graph from disabled command startup while preserving enabled init/capture/flush behavior; focused tests and live local Sentry/telemetry gate passed.
body: "## Problem\ncpu-prof attribution (2026-07-12, evidence on pm-mi2x notes) shows ~60% of every pm command's wall time at 1.7k items is Node ESM resolve+compile of the @sentry/node -> OpenTelemetry -> undici dependency forest, triggered by the static `import * as SentryModule from \"@sentry/node\"` at the top of src/core/sentry/instrument.ts. Isolated: `await import(\"@sentry/node\")` = 847ms while `commander` = 10ms. The cost is paid even when PM_SENTRY_DISABLED=1 because the opt-out check executes only after module load.\n\n## Fix shape\ninstrument.ts is the SOLE importer and already funnels all access through async ensureSentryInit() / sync getSentry() (undefined until init). Replace the static namespace import with `const SentryModule = (await import(\"@sentry/node\"))` inside ensureSentryInit AFTER the disabled gate; type positions move to `type SentryLike = typeof import(\"@sentry/node\")` (type-only, erased at runtime). Callers in src/cli/main.ts kick ensureSentryInit off non-blocking; sentryCaptureCliError/sentryFlush in src/core/sentry/helpers.ts must await the init promise instead of relying on getSentry() being populated synchronously.\n\n## Semantics preserved (zero feature loss)\n- Telemetry-enabled runs still init Sentry every command; capture/flush await init so no events are dropped at exit.\n- captureConsoleIntegration attaches marginally later; console output emitted before init completes is the only theoretical gap — for enabled runs init resolves in the first ~200ms while the command is still doing fs I/O.\n- Disabled runs (env opt-out, vitest) skip the module graph entirely — this is where the full ~850ms comes back.\n\n## Evidence ceiling\nProduction layout with @sentry/node aliased to an empty stub: pm list 562-801ms vs 1400ms baseline, output byte-identical (mi2x attribution note). Fits accepted ADR pm-irp1 (lazy per-command imports, external deps unchanged)."
